      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">26 January 1866. ¶  ¶ I can accompany these travel notes from Mr Giles and his map only with a few hasty words, esteemed Professor, as I have so very little time during this season of extraordinary dr...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">66.01.26a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To August Petermann</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Sammlung Perthes Archiv,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">SPA ARCH<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">PGM<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">328</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Forschungsbibliothek Gotha der Universität Erfurt</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Petermann: 'Erh. 24. März 1866' [Received 24 March 1866].<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>For a published version of this letter,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>see Voigt (1996),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>p. 76.</p>
               </note>26/1/66</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Nur mit ein paar eiligen Worten kann ich, verehrter Herr Professor, diese Reisenotizen von Mr Giles u seine Karte begleiten, da es mir an Zeit gar sehr gebricht in dieser Jahreszeit ausserordentlicher Dürre, die auch meine Gartendirectur erschwert. Die Casuarina, deren Giles erwähnt, ist C. rigida Miquel; der Cottonbush = Sclerolaena paradoxa R.Brown, die Owenia = O. acidula Ferd Mueller, The spotted tree = Flindersia Strzeleckiana Ferd Mueller, der Baum mit den scharf schmeckenden Blättern ist Codonocarpus cotinifolius Ferd Mueller —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Über die Unglücksfälle, welche M'Intyres Parthie betrafen muss ich mit nächster Post berichten, da noch keine officiellen Depeschen angelangt sind. Nach Privatnachrichten (die ich einstweilen geheim zu halten bitte)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>hat M'Intyre eine schöne Position südlich von dem Coopers Creek verlassen ist vorgedrungen zu einem Platz am Flusse, den er in 2 früheren Jahren besucht, fand dort das Flussbett wasserleer. Auf dem Rückzug geht er voran um Wasser herbei zuschaffen. In seiner Abwesenheit vertheilt der Arzt den für Kranke mitgenommenen Brantwein, u unter dem Einfluss des Getränks werden die armen Pferde die 4 Tage kein Wasser hatten losgelassen ohne <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>einmal (was grässlich ist) sie des Gepäcks zu entledigen, trotz dessen, dass die Parthie nur 24 Stunden ohne Wasser war. So wurden Gepäck Sättel u sw. u 70 Pferde verloren. Die 12 Camele sind gerettet. Uns, die wir hier das ganze anordneten, kann kein Tadel treffen. Wir hatten nicht Fond genug um die Kameele nach Port Denison oder dem Carp. Golf zu bringen bei Schiff. M'Intyre hatte auch seine Pferde u Ausrüstung schon am Paroo von der frühern Reise.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Stets der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Eine neue Karte sende ich Ihnen über Paris per Schiff.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">26 January 1866.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I can accompany these travel notes from Mr Giles and his map only with a few hasty words, esteemed Professor, as I have so very little time during this season of extraordinary drought, which is making the management of the Gardens more difficult<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for me.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Casuarina</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>mentioned by Giles is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">C. rigida</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Miquel, the cotton bush is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Sclerolaena paradoxa</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>R. Brown, the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Owenia</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">O. acidula</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>F. Mueller, the spotted tree<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Flindersia strzeleckiana</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>F. Mueller, the tree with the sharp-tasting leaves is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Codonocarpus cotinifolius</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>F. Mueller.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Notes and map not found.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>In January 1865<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Ernest<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Giles, accompanied by W. H. Tietkens, 'left Melbourne for the country west of the Darling … to take up land for a Melbourne<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>syndicate', and travelled from Wlicannia to Milparinka (both NSW) and back.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(W. H. Tietkens to E. B. Dow,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>4 September 1923, quoted in Dow (1937).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>See also Ericksen (1978), pp. 19-21.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I must report about the misfortunes<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that befell M'Intyre's party<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Duncan McIntyre, with the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Ladies' Leichhardt Search Expedition,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1865-6.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with the next mail, as so far no official messages have arrived. According to private news (which I ask you to keep to yourself for the present), M'Intyre had left a good site south of Cooper's Creek<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Qld.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and proceeded to a locality at the river, that he had visited twice in previous years, but he found the river bed dry. On the return journey he went on ahead to procure water. During his absence the doctor<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James Murray, who accompanied the expedition as medical doctor, naturalist and second-in-command to McIntyre.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>distributed the brandy that had been brought in case of sickness, and under the influence of the drink the poor horses, that had had no water for four days, were let loose without even (it is horrible) unloading their packs, even though the party had only been without water for 24 hours. Thus packs, saddles<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and 70 horses were lost. The 12 camels have been saved. We,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M and the Ladies' Committee.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>who organised all this, are beyond reproach. We did not have sufficient funds to transport the camels by ship to Port Denison<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Now<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Bowen,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Qld.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>or the Gulf of Carpentaria. Also, M'Intyre already had his horses and equipment at the Paroo<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Paroo River,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Qld.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from his earlier travels.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I am sending you a new map by ship via Paris.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Map not identified.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Casuarina<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>rigida</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Codonocarpus cotinifolius</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Flindersia strzeleckiana</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Owenia<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>acidula</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sclerolaena paradoxa</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
